<!-- qartez-mcp-instructions -->
## Qartez MCP ‚Äî MANDATORY Tool Priority

When the `qartez` MCP server is available, you MUST use its tools INSTEAD OF built-in `Glob`, `Grep`, and `Read` for codebase exploration. This is enforced by a PreToolUse hook ‚Äî `Glob` and `Grep` will be DENIED when `.qartez/` exists.

**Tool mapping (MUST follow):**

| Instead of | MUST use | When |
|---|---|---|
| `Glob` | `qartez_map` | Understanding project structure, finding files |
| `Grep` | `qartez_grep` | Searching for symbols, functions, types |
| `Grep` | `qartez_find` | Looking up specific symbol definitions |
| `Read` | `qartez_read` | Reading symbol source code with context |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_impact` | BEFORE modifying any heavily-imported file |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_cochange` | Understanding which files change together |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_unused` | Finding dead/unused code |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_refs` | Finding all references to a symbol |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_project` | Getting full project statistics |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_move` | Moving a symbol between files |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_rename` | Renaming a symbol across the codebase |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_rename_file` | Renaming a file and updating all imports |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_outline` | Getting symbol outline of a file (names, kinds, lines) |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_deps` | Viewing file dependency edges (imports/exports) |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_stats` | Language/LOC/symbol-count breakdown (project or per-file) |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_calls` | Call hierarchy: who calls a function and what it calls |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_context` | Finding related files for a set of files you plan to modify |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_hotspots` | Finding high-risk code: complexity x coupling x churn |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_clones` | Detecting duplicate code (same AST shape) for refactoring |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_wiki` | Generating architecture wiki via community detection |
| ‚Äî | `qartez_boundaries` | Checking architecture boundary rules (.qartez/boundaries.toml) |

**Workflow:**
1. `qartez_map` ‚Äî understand project structure first
2. `qartez_find` / `qartez_grep` ‚Äî locate symbols
3. `qartez_read` ‚Äî read code with semantic context
4. `qartez_impact` ‚Äî check before modifying exports

**Analysis tools (use proactively):**
- `qartez_outline` before reviewing a file (cheaper than reading the full source)
- `qartez_deps` to understand what a file imports/exports
- `qartez_calls` to trace call chains when debugging
- `qartez_context` before starting a multi-file change (surfaces files you might miss)
- `qartez_hotspots` before refactoring (identifies highest-risk areas)
- `qartez_clones` when looking for refactoring opportunities
- `qartez_wiki` to generate an architecture overview document
- `qartez_boundaries` to check/enforce module boundary rules

**Modification guard (ENFORCED):** A PreToolUse hook (`qartez-guard`) blocks `Edit`/`Write`/`MultiEdit` on load-bearing files ‚Äî those with PageRank ‚â• 0.05 OR transitive blast radius ‚â• 10. When blocked, the error tells you exactly which thresholds fired and which file to pass to `qartez_impact`. Calling `qartez_impact file_path=<the file>` acts as an acknowledgment: subsequent edits on that file are allowed for 10 minutes (one conversation turn). Override per-project with env vars `QARTEZ_GUARD_PAGERANK_MIN`, `QARTEZ_GUARD_BLAST_MIN`, `QARTEZ_GUARD_ACK_TTL_SECS`, or disable with `QARTEZ_GUARD_DISABLE=1`.

**Canned workflow prompts (MCP slash commands):**

Qartez ships five prompt templates that orchestrate the tools above. Invoke them as slash commands when the task matches:

- `/qartez_review <file>` ‚Äî code review: blast radius + outline + references + co-change
- `/qartez_architecture [top_n]` ‚Äî one-minute architecture overview grounded in PageRank
- `/qartez_debug <symbol>` ‚Äî find + read + call hierarchy + references in one shot
- `/qartez_onboard [area]` ‚Äî five-file onboarding reading list, optionally focused on an area
- `/qartez_pre_merge <files>` ‚Äî pre-merge safety check across the changed files

**Fallback:** Use `Glob`/`Grep`/`Read` ONLY for non-code content (config files, text search, file patterns that qartez cannot handle).
